        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "For me, eating outside is not really about satiating hunger. If I can cook at home, then I will cook at home. If I'm tired, I'll grab something cheap or tried-and-tested. You'll see that mentality reflected in the lower numbers. I like to keep eating outside an experience. It's not just the taste, but it's also the setting, the memories, and how I feel aside from no longer being hungry. Sometimes you'll feel disappointed trying unknown things, but I think it's part of figuring out better things than what you already know or have. "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": null,
              "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exploration%E2%80%93exploitation_dilemma",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "Don't get stuck in a local maxima"
                }
              ],
              "label": "Don't get stuck in a local maxima",
              "identifier": "don't get stuck in a local maxima"
            }
          ]
